The paper deals with the quantifier alternation hierarchy in first-order logic over finite words with linear order and binary successor predicate. This falls under the area of logic and automata theory, which is covered by cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) and cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory). The paper also discusses the alternation hierarchy of temporal logic, which is related to computational complexity and circuit complexity, covered by cs.CC (Computational Complexity) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Finally, the paper presents a decidable algorithm, which is related to decidability and complexity theory, covered by cs.LG (Machine Learning).
